Malabar Cements Ltd. is seeking
48,000 metric tons of imported thermal coal, according to a
document on its  website .  The Kerala-based state-owned cement maker is seeking coal
with 6,300 kilocalorie per kilogram air-dried basis, 12 percent
maximum total moisture, 15 percent maximum ash and 1 percent
maximum sulfur to be delivered at Cochin port, according to the
tender document. It closes Aug. 29, and bids will be opened on
Aug. 31.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dinakar Sethuraman in  Singapore  at 
 dinakar@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
